[metadata]
Name:Aladdin gains control of an artifact (1994 compat B1)
Goal:Win
Difficulty:Easy

# Regression for the 1994 World Championship compat sweep (mtg-713 B1).
# Aladdin: "{1}{R}{R}, {T}: Gain control of target artifact for as long as you
# control Aladdin." Script:
#   A:AB$ GainControl | Cost$ 1 R R T | ValidTgts$ Artifact | LoseControl$ LeavesPlay,LoseControl
#
# Bug: `get_valid_targets_for_ability` (targeting.rs) had no GainControl arm (the
# spell path did), AND the activated-ability placeholder-rewrite in priority.rs
# had no GainControl arm, so the ability enumerated zero targets / its target +
# new_controller stayed placeholders and execute_effect bailed — Aladdin's
# ability was never offered / never stole anything. Effect::GainControl also
# carried no ValidTgts restriction and only a binary until_eot duration.
#
# Fix: Effect::GainControl now carries a structured ControlDuration + a
# TargetRestriction; the converter parses ValidTgts$/LoseControl$; both
# targeting + activation paths resolve the target/controller/source; and a new
# self-correcting `recompute_source_control` SBA pass reverts control to the
# owner the moment the grantee stops controlling the source (Aladdin leaves play
# or is itself stolen) — CR 800.4a.
#
# Setup: P0 controls Aladdin + 3 Mountains (for {1}{R}{R}); P1 controls a Mox
# Ruby. The e2e test exercises: (1) Aladdin's ability lists Mox Ruby as a legal
# target; (2) resolving it puts Mox Ruby under P0 with a recorded control grant;
# (3) once Aladdin leaves the battlefield, the next SBA returns Mox Ruby to P1.
[state]
turn=2
activeplayer=p0
activephase=Main1
p0life=20
p0battlefield=Aladdin; Mountain; Mountain; Mountain
p0library=Mountain; Mountain; Mountain

p1life=20
p1battlefield=Mox Ruby
p1library=Forest; Forest; Forest
